cumentary perspectives on Alberta treaties. It has been twice cited in landmark decisions by the Supreme Court of Canada since its original publication in 1979. Expanded, and with a new introduction by Richard Price, this third edition supports a growing understanding between leaders of government and First Nations people in Alberta and Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIndians of North AmericazAlbertaxGovernment relations. 0aIndians of North AmericazAlbertaxTreaties. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh  aHistory.  aNative Studies.1 aBottle, Camoose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuffalo, Annie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuffalo, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaniel, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoster, J.E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriesen, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGibot, Felix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHickey, Lynn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorse, Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Gordon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLightening, Richard L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMustus, Jean-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOkeymaw, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Chiese, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, Richard T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoan, Lazarus, econtr